Nineteen years is certainly a long time; and even if you don't wear them much, your old one must have lasted well.

What was the name of the tailor?
Philipson. It's quite a small shop right at the end of King street.

Very trusting of you. It is, as a matter of fact.

I don't think so, thank you. Good morning.
